    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 25,
      "text": "Tele. Room",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 26,
      "text": "Mr. Nease",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 27,
      "text": "Miss Holmes",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 28,
      "text": "Miss Gandy",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 29,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 30,
      "text": "The Bureau was requested by the Air Forces Intelligence to assist",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 31,
      "text": "the Air Forces in attempting to arrive at an explanation of the above",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 32,
      "text": "phenomena. The Air Forces indicated that the alleged sightings of flying",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 33,
      "text": "discs might have been made by individuals of Communist sympathies for the",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 34,
      "text": "purpose of causing mass hysteria in the United States over the fear of a secret",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 35,
      "text": "Russian weapon. The Bureau agreed to assist in the investigation of the reported",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 36,
      "text": "sightings, and the Field was advised in Bureau Bulletin No. 42, Series 1947, dated",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 37,
      "text": "July 30, 1947, that they should investigate each instance which was brought to",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 38,
      "text": "their attention of the sighting of a flying disc in order to ascertain whether or",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 39,
      "text": "not it was a bona fide sighting, an imaginary one, or a prank. The results of the",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 40,
      "text": "investigation conducted by the Bureau Field Offices in this matter have failed to",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 41,
      "text": "reveal any indication of subversive individuals being involved in any of the",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 42,
      "text": "reported sightings.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 43,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 44,
      "text": "The Bureau has received a communication in the captioned matter from",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 45,
      "text": "the Special Agent in Charge at San Francisco, dated September 19, 1947, which",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 46,
      "text": "attached a \"restricted\" letter that was furnished confidentially to the SAC at",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 47,
      "text": "San Francisco by Lieutenant Colonel Donald L. Springer, A-2, Army Air Forces,",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 48,
      "text": "Hamilton Field, California, a copy of which is attached hereto. It is noted",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 49,
      "text": "that the letter, which is dated September 3, 1947, is signed \"By Command of",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 50,
      "text": "Lieutenant General Stratemeyer\" by Colonel R. H. Smith, Assistant Chief of Staff",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 51,
      "text": "Intelligence, Headquarters, Air Defense Command, Mitchel Field, New York, and is",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 52,
      "text": "addressed to the Commanding Generals of the various Air Forces. This letter is",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 53,
      "text": "entitled \"Cooperation of FBI with AAF on Investigations of 'Flying Disc' Incidents.\"",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 54,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 55,
      "text": "This letter states in substance that it was the original intent of the",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 56,
      "text": "AC/AS-2, Headquarters, Army Air Forces that whereas the ADC Air Forces would",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 57,
      "text": "interview responsible observers, the FBI would investigate incidents of so-called",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 58,
      "text": "discs being found on the ground. Further, it indicates that the services of the",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 59,
      "text": "FBI were enlisted in order to relieve the numbered Air Forces of the task of",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 60,
      "text": "tracking down all the many instances which turned out to be \"ash can covers,",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 61,
      "text": "toilet seats and whatnot.\"",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 62,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 63,
      "text": "RECOMMENDATION:",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 64,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 65,
      "text": "It is recommended that the Bureau protest vigorously to the Assistant",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 66,
      "text": "Chief of Air Staff - 2. It is also recommended that the Bureau discontinue all",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 67,
      "text": "activity in this field and that the Bureau Field Offices be advised to discon-",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 68,
      "text": "tinue all investigations and to refer all complaints received to the Air Forces.",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 69,
      "text": "A proposed Bulletin is attached for your approval.",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 70,
      "text": "Attachment.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 71,
      "status": "blank"
    },
